The Siaya government will spend Sh26 million renovating the Migwena Sportsgrounds to meet international standards. Deputy Governor James Okumbe said the county government wants to make Saiya a sports and talent development centre.  The county lacks recreational facilities.Okumbe said a pavilion will be built and field graded. “We are also going to ensure the facility has a standard gate, modern toilets and electricity,” he said. Okumbe spoke in Migwena, Bondo, on Tuesday during the closing ceremony of the annual sports and cultural festival.  The festival is a traditional event and has historical significance. It was used to unify the community and settle differences through sporting and traditional activities. Participants engage in football, athletics and traditional dances.